Introduction

Jeon Jungkook, is a South Korean singer-songwriter, dancer, rapper, producer and composer under Big Hit Entertainment. He is best known as the main vocalist, lead dancer, center, and maknae of the worldwide sensational boy group BTS.

Jungkook used to dream of becoming a professional badminton player, but the moment he saw G-Dragon perform on television, he was inspired to become an idol. Jungkook auditioned for the show 'Super Star K' and although he did not pass, he still received casting offers from different entertainment companies. After watching RM perform, Jungkook chose to be a part of Big Hit Entertainment.

In 2013, Jungkook debuted with the group and went on to become a worlwide phenomenon.

Jungkook made his solo debut with single "Seven" on July 14, 2023 featuring American rapper Latto, and released his second solo single, "3D", featuring Jack Harlow, on September 29. His first studio album "Golden" was published on November of the same year featuring title track "Standing Next to You".
